> create a folder called css in assets
> create a file called style.scss
> open ruby command as admin
> hit C: (what ever the directory you are in)
> hit the path you are in (css-->style.scss)


> gem install compass

YOU GOT AN ERROR WHILE INSTALLING THIS
REFER https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27435841/windows-7-64-bit-could-not-find-a-valid-gem-compass-0-here-is-why-unab

		1. DOWNLOAD  http://curl.haxx.se/ca/cacert.pem
		2. save the file anywhere Ex: in drive C:
		C:\cacert.pem
		3. set SSL_CERT_FILE=C:\cacert.pem
		4. now try gem install compass
